Explanation
 
BACKGROUND:
This ordinance approves the acceptance of certain territory (AN24-005) by the city of Columbus. The Ohio Revised Code stipulates that to be effective, City acceptance must take place a minimum of 60 days from the receipt by the City Clerk of the approval notice from the county. If City Council does not accept the ordinance within 120 days of its first consideration, the annexation will be considered rejected. This petition was filed with Franklin County on May 30, 2024. City Council approved a service ordinance addressing the site on June 10, 2024. Franklin County approved the annexation on July 23, 2024 and the City Clerk received notice on August 2, 2024. 
FISCAL IMPACT: 
Provision of municipal services does represent cost to the City; however, the annexation of land also has the potential to create revenue to the City.
 
 
Title
 
To accept the application (AN24-005) of Abbasi Farms et al for the annexation of certain territory containing 132.47± acres in Brown Township. ($0.00)
 
 
Body
 
WHEREAS, a petition for the annexation of certain territory in Brown Township was filed on behalf of Abbasi Farms et.al., on May 30, 2024; and
WHEREAS, the petition was considered and approved by the Franklin County Board of Commissioners at a hearing on July 23, 2024; and
WHEREAS, on August 2, 2024, the City Clerk received from Franklin County a certified copy of the resolution addressing the petition; and
WHEREAS, sixty days have now elapsed since receipt of the resolution in accordance with the provisions of the Ohio Revised Code; and 
WHEREAS, it is in the best interest of the city of Columbus to accept the annexation of the territory addressed by the petition; NOW, THEREFORE, 
BE IT ORDAINED BY THE COUNCIL OF THE CITY OF COLUMBUS:
SECTION 1. That the annexation proposed by Abbasi Farms et al in a petition filed with the Franklin County Board of Commissioners on May 30, 2024 and subsequently approved by the Board on July 23, 2024 is hereby accepted and said territory is hereby annexed to the city of Columbus. Said territory is described as follows:
